WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:34.835 --> 00:41.775
[Choir singing]

02:10.631 --> 02:15.336
(Adira narrating)
This story, although set
in the past, is about the future

02:17.238 --> 02:19.673
Where I know freedom is.

02:24.478 --> 02:26.747
In the smallest of things

02:27.981 --> 02:31.285
I see the flicker of hope.

02:31.319 --> 02:35.289
[Soft background music]

02:35.956 --> 02:39.693
[Fire crackling]

02:44.565 --> 02:47.167
[Chains rattling]

03:02.416 --> 03:04.685
[Gentle murmurs]

03:04.718 --> 03:06.687
[Door creaking]

03:06.720 --> 03:09.423
[Feet rustling]

03:12.260 --> 03:16.830
[Horse snorting]
[Hooves clicking]

03:23.036 --> 03:24.805
The keys, Samuel.

03:26.374 --> 03:27.408
[Door creaking]

03:31.979 --> 03:36.617
[Key and chains rattling]

03:41.989 --> 03:43.724
[Hooves clicking]

03:43.757 --> 03:44.958
[Knocking]

03:46.860 --> 03:49.730
[Distant clicking of hooves]

03:52.433 --> 03:54.368
[Horse snorting]

03:55.336 --> 03:56.904
[Door knocking]

03:56.937 --> 03:58.339
Go.

03:58.372 --> 04:00.441
[Rustling noises]

04:00.474 --> 04:03.411
[Chains rattling]

04:04.412 --> 04:06.347
Go, boy.

04:13.754 --> 04:15.489
Go!
[Feet rustling]

04:15.523 --> 04:19.459
(Adira narrating)
No one can shackle the hope
that is hidden in our hearts.

04:20.694 --> 04:23.531
If only you will believe it,
Samuel.

04:25.098 --> 04:27.000
[Match striking]

04:27.034 --> 04:28.336
You're late.

04:29.036 --> 04:30.971
I got held up.

04:31.004 --> 04:33.441
Had to break up a fight
in one of the cabins.

04:34.842 --> 04:37.745
[Crickets buzzing]

04:43.417 --> 04:47.955
[Rustling sounds]
[Door creaking]

04:49.122 --> 04:52.660
[Crickets buzzing]

04:56.664 --> 04:59.867
Jackson! Robert!
Get the horses!

05:00.434 --> 05:05.706
[Feet rustling]
[Dogs barking and howling]

05:05.739 --> 05:08.709
Didn't hold Jerome
long enough off cabin 15.

05:10.110 --> 05:13.614
You go ahead.
Meet you at the bridge.

05:13.647 --> 05:15.616
I'll fetch them dogs away.

05:16.884 --> 05:18.852
[Gentle pats]
[Commotion in the background]

05:21.655 --> 05:23.056
[Smacking sound]

05:23.090 --> 05:25.393
- God help us.
- God bless you, Big Hand.

05:25.859 --> 05:30.631
[Dogs barking]
[Shuffling sounds]

05:39.740 --> 05:42.410
- There he is!
- Come on! Get him!

05:42.443 --> 05:44.412
He's getting away!
[Drums beating]

05:46.013 --> 05:48.916
[Birds chirping]

05:51.919 --> 05:54.988
[Feet rustling]

05:56.857 --> 05:58.826
[Adira coughing]

06:06.967 --> 06:08.469
(Vanessa)
Are you sure, Samuel?

06:10.504 --> 06:11.972
Yeah.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.608
Where's Big Hand?

06:16.544 --> 06:18.879
He'll be by soon, son.
Come on.

06:21.515 --> 06:23.951
(Adira narrating)
Even as we make our way
toward freedom

06:23.984 --> 06:27.521
Would it ever be possible to
leave behind what we'd endured?

06:27.755 --> 06:29.823
[Scratching and clanging sounds]

06:29.857 --> 06:32.926
[Rattling sounds]
[Water splashing]

06:32.960 --> 06:35.529
[Metal clanging]

06:35.829 --> 06:37.865
Oh, nah-ah!
[Ruckus]

06:38.198 --> 06:40.133
[Woman crying]

06:41.669 --> 06:43.737
[Distant tapping]

06:49.477 --> 06:51.779
[Muffled thumps]

06:52.680 --> 06:53.781
[Whipping sound]

06:55.883 --> 06:57.585
Let's go. Let's go.

07:03.891 --> 07:05.926
Lord have mercy!

07:05.959 --> 07:09.863
[Chains rattling]

07:10.798 --> 07:12.500
[Muffled gasping]

07:18.572 --> 07:21.642
[Heavy breathing]

07:22.075 --> 07:27.147
[Rustling]
[Chains rattling]

07:32.119 --> 07:33.987
[Whipping sound]
[Gasping]

07:34.622 --> 07:38.692
[Big Hand screaming in pain]

07:39.893 --> 07:41.862
[Big Hand moaning]

07:42.295 --> 07:45.999
[Plantation overseer
yelling in rage]

07:52.606 --> 07:54.274
(Plantation slave)
Jesus...

07:54.307 --> 07:56.009
He's had enough!

07:57.244 --> 07:59.847
- He hasn't talked.
- He is nearly unconscious.

08:01.048 --> 08:03.216
[Laboured breathing]

08:03.250 --> 08:04.718
Where are the others?

08:04.752 --> 08:06.987
The others have vanished,
Mr. Monroe.

08:09.056 --> 08:11.058
[Weakly]
Praise God Almighty.

08:12.025 --> 08:13.627
[Loud slapping,
Big Hand yelps]

08:18.265 --> 08:19.633
Where are they?

08:26.674 --> 08:29.042
If they get away
because of your stupidity...

08:29.076 --> 08:30.978
[Fabric rustling]

08:32.846 --> 08:34.815
Now you leave him
strung up, yeah? Mm?

08:35.347 --> 08:37.017
(Monroe)
And get a hold of Plimpton.

08:37.049 --> 08:38.719
Plimpton?

08:38.751 --> 08:40.953
I want my property back
before nightfall.
[Horse snorting]

08:40.988 --> 08:42.823
[Monroe clicks with his mouth]

08:42.856 --> 08:45.826
[Horse hooves pattering]

08:46.093 --> 08:48.528
All of you! Back to work.

08:53.601 --> 08:54.902
Come on, now.

08:59.673 --> 09:04.144
[Tapping and rattling sounds]

09:08.649 --> 09:10.851
[Singing weakly]
* Swing low

09:14.888 --> 09:17.190
* Sweet chariot

09:23.163 --> 09:25.666
* And carry me home

09:28.869 --> 09:30.904
* Swing low

09:32.806 --> 09:35.008
* Sweet chariot

09:36.176 --> 09:38.011
[Gasp]

09:38.045 --> 09:40.714
* Please come
and carry me home *

09:44.785 --> 09:49.623
* If you get there

09:51.124 --> 09:54.261
* Before I do

09:55.963 --> 10:02.035
* Coming to carry me home

10:04.437 --> 10:07.107
* Tell all my friends

10:08.375 --> 10:11.011
* I'm coming too

10:13.914 --> 10:19.252
* Coming to carry me home

10:21.922 --> 10:26.827
[Footsteps]

10:27.961 --> 10:30.263
[Birds chirping]

10:35.102 --> 10:36.636
Samuel?

10:42.109 --> 10:43.643
Samuel Woodward?

10:47.414 --> 10:48.816
[Feet rustling]

10:48.849 --> 10:49.783
Yes sir.

10:52.986 --> 10:54.187
Thomas Garrett.

11:00.227 --> 11:02.062
- Mr. Garrett.
- You must be Vanessa.

11:05.999 --> 11:07.968
Adira? Ma'am.

11:09.737 --> 11:11.171
And this is Jim.

11:13.273 --> 11:14.842
Hello, son.

11:15.442 --> 11:17.044
You've done well.

11:17.410 --> 11:18.846
Big Hand?

11:22.115 --> 11:23.150
I see.

11:28.221 --> 11:29.957
Come on.

11:29.990 --> 11:34.194
[Water lapping]

11:36.029 --> 11:39.099
(Adira narrating)
We begun our long journey
north with Mr. Garrett

11:39.132 --> 11:42.736
On pathways known only
to the Underground Railroad.

11:42.770 --> 11:43.937
[Adira coughing]

11:43.971 --> 11:45.739
(Samuel)
Mr. Garrett! Come on.

11:45.773 --> 11:47.307
(Jim)
Grandma. I got you.

11:47.340 --> 11:48.876
(Adira)
I'm all right.

11:53.280 --> 11:55.315
Woah, woah!

11:57.250 --> 11:59.719
[Horse snorting]

12:12.800 --> 12:17.070
[Feet pattering]

12:17.104 --> 12:18.972
[Door clicking open]

12:26.079 --> 12:29.216
You came.
He's been waiting for you.

12:30.550 --> 12:34.054
[Fire crackling]

12:41.128 --> 12:42.262
(Jerome)
In here.

12:44.131 --> 12:45.465
Mm-hm.

12:48.568 --> 12:50.370
Woulda never happened
in his old man's day.

12:51.872 --> 12:53.006
I heard tell...

12:53.040 --> 12:54.875
(Monroe interrupting)
My father was a fool, Plimpton.

12:54.908 --> 12:57.410
Took the concept
of Christian charity too far.

12:57.978 --> 12:58.912
Get out.

13:01.514 --> 13:03.316
Slave's expensive, Plimpton.

13:03.350 --> 13:05.152
And the Underground Railroad now

13:05.185 --> 13:07.888
They are targeting
slave owners in Virginia.

13:08.421 --> 13:09.990
I'm retired.

13:10.958 --> 13:12.159
[Soft thump]

13:12.192 --> 13:14.061
And there's more when
they all get recaptured.

13:15.028 --> 13:17.898
All? What,
there's more than one?

13:18.365 --> 13:22.836
There's Samuel, his son,
the old woman, and Vanessa.

13:22.870 --> 13:25.138
They're gonna be easy to track.

13:25.172 --> 13:28.541
No slave has ever escaped
from my plantation.
[Liquid sloshing]

13:30.110 --> 13:31.979
Why don't you send Jerome?

13:32.445 --> 13:34.247
(Monroe)
I want them back
before they insight the others.

13:35.248 --> 13:36.816
Garrett's part of it.

13:37.918 --> 13:39.452
Garrett?

13:39.486 --> 13:42.389
Him and his Quaker cohort they
are a menace to our industry.

13:42.422 --> 13:44.958
The entire economy
of Virginia is at risk.

13:45.926 --> 13:48.996
Monroe, I am no longer
in the slave hunting business.

13:49.029 --> 13:51.531
Now, now, you just -
you made a mistake, Plimpton.

13:52.599 --> 13:53.967
Made you weak.

13:55.268 --> 13:58.171
(Monroe)
Don't let your conscience
get in the way of business.

13:59.606 --> 14:01.474
How's 500 dollars?

14:02.142 --> 14:04.444
I'll give you another thousand
when you bring

14:05.345 --> 14:06.980
(Monroe)
And that's including Vanessa.

14:08.248 --> 14:09.616
Oh, you can't let her go,
can ya?

14:13.286 --> 14:15.022
[Slurping sound]

14:16.623 --> 14:18.425
How

14:18.458 --> 14:21.494
She's of no use to me.
She's too old and too sick.

14:23.430 --> 14:24.965
They're gonna be headed north.

14:24.998 --> 14:26.900
I'm sending one of my boys
with you.

14:26.934 --> 14:28.135
I don't need a babysitter.

14:28.168 --> 14:29.502
He will look after my interest.

14:31.071 --> 14:33.040
They will all be in church
on Sunday.

14:34.074 --> 14:35.208
[Coin tinkling]

14:36.609 --> 14:38.578
(Monroe)
Get yourself a shave.

14:40.547 --> 14:44.517
[Crickets chirping]

15:04.604 --> 15:05.605
You've done well.

15:06.739 --> 15:08.942
Most don't make it this far.

15:08.976 --> 15:11.078
We had help, Mr. Garrett.

15:12.312 --> 15:13.613
Jim.

15:17.517 --> 15:19.419
(Vanessa)
Thank you, Mr. Garrett.

15:19.452 --> 15:21.321
Our lives have been...
[Fire crackling]

15:23.123 --> 15:25.158
Adira's been a slave
all her life.

15:26.393 --> 15:29.162
And my son has never seen
the sun rise

15:29.196 --> 15:30.597
Without the threat
of a whipping.

15:32.399 --> 15:34.467
One day, we pray.

15:34.501 --> 15:36.603
Ain't be the white man's God
she pray to.

15:36.636 --> 15:37.670
Samuel...

15:38.538 --> 15:41.241
Freedom, Samuel.
God willing.

15:42.409 --> 15:44.044
(Garrett)
Freedom.

15:44.077 --> 15:45.012
[Samuel scoffs]

15:49.582 --> 15:51.084
Why you do this, Mr. Garrett?

15:52.485 --> 15:54.221
Sammy, you have to trust.

15:55.255 --> 15:57.224
Like your momma trusted Monroe?

15:59.592 --> 16:01.628
He gonna want you back, Nessa.
[Vanessa sighs]

16:01.661 --> 16:02.662
You're his blood.

16:06.299 --> 16:12.205
[Adira humming
Amazing Grace]

16:17.377 --> 16:21.748
(Adira)
* Twas grace that brought us

16:21.781 --> 16:25.285
* Safe thus far

16:26.319 --> 16:31.624
[Humming continues]

16:31.658 --> 16:33.293
Pa used to sing that song.

16:34.794 --> 16:37.164
He loved to sing.

16:38.431 --> 16:40.233
You refuse to sing.

16:41.568 --> 16:43.670
(Adira)
One day you will, son.

16:45.238 --> 16:47.707
Amazing Grace.

16:49.576 --> 16:51.278
That saved a wretch like me?

16:53.213 --> 16:56.249
I was Jim's age
when I first heard it.

16:57.484 --> 17:00.287
And the story of the man
who wrote it.

17:01.521 --> 17:03.456
An infamous slave trader.

17:05.092 --> 17:06.626
(Adira)
A wretch like you, Samuel.

17:09.529 --> 17:12.499
But he loved to sing.
[Men laughing in the background]

17:13.099 --> 17:16.236
* Kings and queens
And oh the man in the moon *

17:16.269 --> 17:20.339
* A broken mirror doesn't mean
That someone will die soon *
[Footsteps]

17:21.540 --> 17:25.244
* A black cat isn't all bad luck
And redheads won't sink a boat *
[Cups clicking]

17:26.546 --> 17:30.350
* If you're drowning in the sea
Will God keep you afloat? *

17:30.650 --> 17:33.320
Yeah!

17:33.353 --> 17:35.722
Get out!
[Ruckus]
[Men yelling and laughing]

17:38.258 --> 17:40.393
[Soft background music]

17:40.427 --> 17:42.495
Congratulation, Captain Newton.

17:42.529 --> 17:44.297
Thank you, Mr. Barton.

17:44.331 --> 17:46.533
Oh, and, uh, bravo!

17:46.566 --> 17:48.668
I remember a song you wrote
about old captain Pennrose.

17:49.436 --> 17:52.071
Cruel, Newton, but very witty.

17:53.273 --> 17:55.275
But I cannot believe
you actually bought shares

17:55.308 --> 17:56.576
On the

17:57.277 --> 17:59.279
After Pennrose died,
I acquired his half

17:59.312 --> 18:01.114
And am now in partnership
with Amos Clowe.

18:02.749 --> 18:04.284
Amos Clowe?

18:04.317 --> 18:07.420
Clowe owns the slave factory
on the Plantain Islands

18:07.454 --> 18:09.789
And this will be our
first shipment to Charleston.

18:12.259 --> 18:15.428
I know you've had difficulties
with Amos, Newton.

18:15.462 --> 18:17.364
He promised me
an apprenticeship, Barton

18:18.631 --> 18:20.300
But he treated me
like an animal.

18:20.867 --> 18:22.369
Like one of his slaves.

18:22.402 --> 18:25.638
He actually chained
and starved me for 18 months.

18:25.672 --> 18:27.507
It's all in the past.

18:28.708 --> 18:30.343
It's all a means to a good end.

18:30.377 --> 18:32.245
[Footsteps]

18:32.279 --> 18:33.680
And now, as we always planned

18:33.713 --> 18:35.615
You have the opportunity
to share in the profits

18:36.383 --> 18:37.717
Captain Newton.

18:38.985 --> 18:41.421
Now, I have to go to Charleston
to set up the slave market.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.323
I'll meet you there
on your arrival.

18:43.956 --> 18:46.759
Time is against us.
I need you to leave this week

18:46.793 --> 18:49.296
To pick up the first load
in Africa.

18:49.329 --> 18:50.663
But, Mary.

18:50.697 --> 18:53.333
Your fiancée
will want for nothing.
[Soft thud]

18:54.601 --> 18:56.869
That's a lot of money, Newton.

18:58.271 --> 19:00.407
Now, the first mate, Davey,
will take care of the cargo.

19:00.440 --> 19:02.675
I'll be giving you
one of Amos' slaves

19:02.709 --> 19:03.743
He'll interpret for you.

19:03.776 --> 19:05.412
Name's Ozias.

19:05.712 --> 19:07.414
[Soft background music]

19:07.447 --> 19:11.751
My business
is now your business.

19:13.586 --> 19:14.787
To ambition.

19:15.322 --> 19:16.523
[Cups clicking]

19:18.658 --> 19:20.293
[Thumps]

19:21.428 --> 19:22.762
Good luck, Newton.

19:28.535 --> 19:30.203
[Newton sighing]

19:34.907 --> 19:36.543
[Church bell ringing]
It is blood money.

19:36.576 --> 19:38.878
Mary, I'm simply the captain
of Barton's ship.

19:38.911 --> 19:41.381
I don't own it, nor the cargo.

19:41.414 --> 19:43.350
To me, and I'm sure
to your fellow parishioners

19:43.383 --> 19:44.984
And most of this nation,
it is just business.

19:45.017 --> 19:47.520
You speak of business
and I speak of your soul.

19:47.554 --> 19:49.822
- Let's not argue, please.
- A soul that I love.

19:49.856 --> 19:51.691
Mary! Mr. Newton!

19:55.027 --> 19:56.896
We'll marry as soon as I return.

19:57.597 --> 19:59.499
I only pray that God allows it.
[Choir singing]

19:59.532 --> 20:01.601
I'll be away
for six to eight months.

20:02.034 --> 20:03.970
You know the perils of the sea.
If I don't return...

20:04.003 --> 20:05.605
- John...
- If I don't come back...

20:05.638 --> 20:06.739
I need to know
you'll be cared for.

20:06.773 --> 20:08.675
I don't want you to go.

20:09.842 --> 20:11.878
I fear this time
I shall never see you again.

20:11.911 --> 20:14.213
(Charlotte)
Mr. Newton!

20:19.352 --> 20:21.654
I shall pray every day
for your return.

20:22.722 --> 20:24.457
Have faith, Mary.

20:24.991 --> 20:26.826
I do.
[Smacking sound]

20:26.859 --> 20:29.296
John, I do.

20:35.402 --> 20:38.638
[Choir singing
in the background]

20:39.739 --> 20:44.611
* It is well

20:45.077 --> 20:50.283
* With my soul

20:50.550 --> 20:53.286
* It is well

20:53.320 --> 20:59.992
* It is well with my soul

21:00.560 --> 21:07.567
[Music continues]

21:07.600 --> 21:12.705
* Though Satan should buffet

21:12.739 --> 21:17.710
* Though trials should come

21:17.744 --> 21:24.617
* Let this blest assurance
control *

21:25.918 --> 21:30.890
* That Christ hath regarded
[People murmuring]
[Screams]

21:30.923 --> 21:34.994
* My helpless estate

21:35.027 --> 21:38.365
* And hath shed

21:38.398 --> 21:44.904
* His own blood for my soul
[Chains rattling]
[People yelling]

21:46.739 --> 21:50.510
* It is well

21:51.010 --> 21:52.712
[Sizzling]
[Woman howling in pain]

21:52.745 --> 21:55.715
* with my soul

21:55.748 --> 21:57.550
[Woman pleading]

21:57.584 --> 21:59.486
* It is well

21:59.519 --> 22:01.120
(Slave trader)
Come on, keep it moving.

22:01.153 --> 22:06.058
* It is well with my soul
[Murmuring and screaming]

22:10.697 --> 22:14.367
[Unintelligible chattering]

22:15.502 --> 22:18.337
(Slave trader)
One seven, move along. 148.

22:20.873 --> 22:22.575
No...

22:24.544 --> 22:26.679
Welcome aboard, Captain Newton.

22:26.713 --> 22:28.881
- Is it Davey?
- Yes, sir. Your first mate.

22:31.484 --> 22:32.852
One moment, Mr. Davey.

22:36.756 --> 22:38.057
(Newton)
Ozias.

22:39.358 --> 22:41.594
(Bosun)
Captain Newton, the trunk's
already in your cabin.

22:42.495 --> 22:43.996
- Thank you, Bosun.
- Bless you, sir.

22:44.030 --> 22:45.364
Welcome on board the Pegasus.

22:47.934 --> 22:50.403
Get back to work, slave.

22:51.070 --> 22:53.039
(Slave trader)
That one there.
Pick him up.

22:54.907 --> 22:57.009
[Man panting]

22:57.043 --> 22:58.110
Come on.

22:58.778 --> 23:02.649
No... no...
[Speaking Gambian dialect]

23:03.082 --> 23:04.417
(Slave)
No, no, no...

23:04.451 --> 23:07.854
(Adira narrating)
He set sail that day
to a new world.

23:07.887 --> 23:10.089
A soul without a compass...

23:10.122 --> 23:11.591
Like you Samuel...

23:12.224 --> 23:13.860
Confused...

23:13.893 --> 23:15.728
Confronted by his past.

23:17.196 --> 23:19.065
Desperately hoping

23:19.799 --> 23:21.968
To find his freedom
and his fortune

23:24.671 --> 23:26.773
On a slave ship.

23:28.040 --> 23:29.842
Have faith, Samuel.

23:48.160 --> 23:51.030
[Birds chirping]

23:51.063 --> 23:53.633
[Hooves pattering]

23:57.570 --> 23:59.972
Whoah.
Usual conditions, Plimpton.

24:02.942 --> 24:03.876
Always a pleasure.

24:05.077 --> 24:07.046
We got a family of slaves
this time, Clem.

24:07.880 --> 24:09.215
(Plimpton)
I sent word on ahead.

24:09.248 --> 24:10.449
Who's this?

24:10.917 --> 24:12.619
He's here as my watchdog.

24:13.986 --> 24:16.122
I said be ready at sunrise, boy.

24:16.923 --> 24:19.225
If you ride with me, you follow
my orders, you understand?

24:19.892 --> 24:22.194
We won't have a problem,
Mr. Plimpton. Who's this?

24:23.563 --> 24:24.897
He's my tracker, Clem.

24:25.832 --> 24:27.133
Do we bring them back
dead or alive?

24:28.134 --> 24:29.536
We bring

24:30.169 --> 24:31.571
That's a damn shame.

24:32.304 --> 24:33.940
Mm-hm.

24:34.974 --> 24:36.609
Come on, let's get going.

24:37.076 --> 24:38.878
Come on, come on.
[Hooves pattering]

24:39.779 --> 24:41.948
[Adira coughing]

24:41.981 --> 24:43.249
I got you, momma.

24:43.282 --> 24:44.651
We're nearly there.

24:46.553 --> 24:47.854
Come on.

24:48.888 --> 24:50.890
[People singing
in the background]

24:52.124 --> 24:54.193
(Garrett)
Ha! There's the cavalry.

24:54.226 --> 24:55.528
(Garrett)
Right on time.

24:56.295 --> 25:00.032
[Singing continues]

25:03.803 --> 25:05.605
(McGee)
Who comes here?
Mr. Garrett.

25:06.105 --> 25:07.907
It's been a long time, sir.

25:07.940 --> 25:09.876
- Mr. McGee.
- Very good to see you.

25:10.276 --> 25:12.078
Hey, Pete.
Made quite a stretch sir.

25:12.344 --> 25:14.146
[Thuds]

25:20.853 --> 25:21.954
[Soft thump]

25:23.990 --> 25:25.157
[Chains rattling]

25:30.062 --> 25:31.731
There room for all of us, sir?

25:33.800 --> 25:35.134
Yes, sir.
There's room for all of you.

25:36.235 --> 25:38.170
Even Mr. Garrett.
[Chuckling]

25:39.071 --> 25:40.673
Alright, come on.

25:42.609 --> 25:45.044
Ma'am.
[Adira coughing]

25:45.077 --> 25:46.613
You'll connect with Philips

25:46.646 --> 25:48.347
With a freight train
off of Philadelphia

25:48.380 --> 25:49.882
Get the family to Woodbridge

25:49.916 --> 25:51.618
And I'll take you there
part of the way.

25:52.885 --> 25:54.186
(McGee)
All right, sir.

25:56.923 --> 25:58.958
(McGee)
Hey, ride up here.

25:59.826 --> 26:01.093
[Gentle taps]

26:01.127 --> 26:02.094
It's fine.

26:10.002 --> 26:13.272
* [Band playing the banjo]

26:13.305 --> 26:15.742
* I'm on my way
(I'm on my way) *

26:15.775 --> 26:17.877
* To Canaan's Land
(To Canaan's Land) *

26:17.910 --> 26:19.946
* I'm on my way
(I'm on my way) *

26:19.979 --> 26:22.281
* To Canaan's Land
(To Canaan's Land) *

26:22.314 --> 26:24.250
* I'm on my way
(I'm on my way) *

26:24.283 --> 26:26.686
* To Canaan's Land

26:26.719 --> 26:28.154
* I'm on my way

26:28.187 --> 26:31.357
* Praise the Lord,
I'm on my way *

26:31.390 --> 26:33.359
* It's a mighty hard road
(It's a mighty hard road) *

26:33.392 --> 26:35.628
* but I'm on my way
(I'm on my way) *

26:35.662 --> 26:37.163
I'm like you, Samuel.

26:37.196 --> 26:38.865
I don't sing.

26:39.666 --> 26:41.000
I'm a Quaker.

26:41.033 --> 26:42.401
* I'm on my way
(I'm on my way) *

26:42.434 --> 26:44.370
* To Canaan's Land

26:44.403 --> 26:45.972
* I'm on my way

26:46.005 --> 26:48.641
* Yes my Lord,
To Canaan's Land *

26:49.208 --> 26:51.143
[Horse snorting]

26:51.177 --> 26:54.213
- Yah!
- How far?

26:55.081 --> 26:56.849
It's a couple miles further on.

27:00.820 --> 27:02.855
Your fellow escapee, Big Hand

27:04.290 --> 27:05.624
He was caught.

27:11.430 --> 27:13.866
We also heard that Monroe
sent Plimpton after you.

27:15.434 --> 27:17.103
How many men he got with

27:17.136 --> 27:18.170
He's got two.

27:20.206 --> 27:22.809
That's it?
We got more that that.

27:22.842 --> 27:24.276
The Railroad doesn't go
out of its way

27:24.310 --> 27:25.712
To confront these people.

27:26.112 --> 27:28.080
Our fate is in God's hands

27:28.881 --> 27:30.817
And we'll protect you
with His guidance.

27:30.850 --> 27:32.418
(McGee)
Gentlemen, we got a problem.

27:32.919 --> 27:35.254
We got two roads blocked,
one just up ahead.

27:36.455 --> 27:38.190
Oh, he must want you back
real bad.

27:39.258 --> 27:41.761
And we're gonna be
exactly what we are.

27:42.995 --> 27:44.931
[Chains rattling]

27:44.964 --> 27:46.198
Slaves.

27:58.244 --> 28:00.346
Woah... ho... ho...

28:03.850 --> 28:07.086
* [Suspense music]

28:09.455 --> 28:11.824
Pa, are they gonna catch us?

28:11.858 --> 28:13.325
Hush up now, boy.

28:13.926 --> 28:15.327
(McGee)
All right.
[Clicks with his mouth]

28:31.143 --> 28:32.378
Hey.

28:35.882 --> 28:37.716
What have we got here?

28:40.019 --> 28:41.420
(Guard)
Hold up.

28:43.189 --> 28:44.356
What's going on here?

28:44.390 --> 28:46.358
Looking for runaways.

28:46.392 --> 28:48.160
All we got's
these miserable slaves.

28:48.861 --> 28:50.162
Uh-huh...

28:51.998 --> 28:54.100
[Horse snorting]

29:04.944 --> 29:06.478
This one ain't so miserable.

29:06.512 --> 29:08.180
[Chuckling]

29:08.214 --> 29:09.882
That's not your property,
mister.

29:09.916 --> 29:11.350
[Gun clicking]

29:11.383 --> 29:13.820
Leave
These ain't runaways.

29:14.921 --> 29:17.489
If they were, I'd take
another trip for you.

29:24.997 --> 29:26.532
[Guard sniffing]

29:27.266 --> 29:31.003
[Chuckling]

29:31.470 --> 29:32.972
(Guard)
All right.

29:35.441 --> 29:37.109
(Guard)
All right, come on through.

29:44.516 --> 29:46.085
Much obliged.

29:55.027 --> 29:56.162
Found sets of tracks, boss.

29:57.096 --> 29:58.297
Garrett's with them alright.

29:58.330 --> 29:59.565
(Clem)
Hey, a wagon.

29:59.598 --> 30:01.033
How long
are you gonna take, Plimpton?

30:01.367 --> 30:03.302
Already a day behind.

30:03.335 --> 30:06.138
Monroe will get his slaves back
Sunday. Let's move.

30:06.438 --> 30:09.308
(Plimpton)
Yah!
Come on.

30:09.341 --> 30:14.446
[Hooves pattering]

30:15.247 --> 30:17.884
We Quakers don't believe
in guns, Samuel

30:17.917 --> 30:21.353
But I am occasionally grateful
that Mr. McGee does.

30:21.954 --> 30:23.555
(McGee)
Should be the last time
you have to wear these.

30:23.589 --> 30:25.457
[Chains rattling]

30:27.493 --> 30:29.195
[Horse snorting]

30:30.596 --> 30:32.298
(McGee)
There you are, Jim.

30:35.134 --> 30:38.337
Valley of the shadow of death

30:38.370 --> 30:40.439
I will fear no evil.

30:42.374 --> 30:45.477
Hope can be found
in the darkest of places.

30:48.614 --> 30:51.450
No one is alone.

30:59.058 --> 31:01.093
(Adira narrating)
Believe me, Samuel.

31:01.693 --> 31:04.196
There's always hope.

31:04.230 --> 31:06.232
[Drums beating rhytmically]

31:06.265 --> 31:09.401
(Adira narrating)
Learn from those
who have gone before you.

31:13.005 --> 31:19.045
(Ozias singing)
* I am a poor pilgrim
of sorrow *

31:20.212 --> 31:26.885
* I'm tossed
in this wide world alone *

31:29.155 --> 31:34.493
* No hope have I for tomorrow

31:36.195 --> 31:39.265
* So I've started

31:39.298 --> 31:46.072
* To make Heaven my home

31:47.373 --> 31:51.110
* Sometimes

31:52.044 --> 31:57.483
* I'm tossed and driven, Lord
[Door creaking]

31:57.516 --> 32:04.290
* Sometimes I don't know

32:05.657 --> 32:11.697
* Where to roam

32:13.365 --> 32:18.204
* But I have heard of

32:18.237 --> 32:25.144
* A city called Heaven

32:27.746 --> 32:31.383
* And I've started

32:31.417 --> 32:36.688
* Making my home

32:38.490 --> 32:42.461
[Footsteps]

32:42.494 --> 32:46.398
* Sometimes

32:46.432 --> 32:52.438
* I'm tossed and driven, Lord

32:52.471 --> 32:59.345
* Sometimes I don't know
[Slave moaning]

32:59.378 --> 33:06.052
* Where to roam
[Slave coughing]

33:08.420 --> 33:14.226
* But I have heard of

33:15.127 --> 33:21.767
* A city called Heaven

33:24.536 --> 33:27.573
* And I've started

33:27.606 --> 33:30.276
* To make Heaven

33:30.309 --> 33:35.547
* My home
[Creaking noises]

33:35.581 --> 33:39.685
[Footsteps]
[Seagulls squawking]

33:40.452 --> 33:42.621
I apologise,
I didn't mean to startle you.

33:43.089 --> 33:45.057
John Newton.

33:45.557 --> 33:47.626
You must think it's strange that
I'm in command of a slave ship

33:47.659 --> 33:49.628
Owned by Amos Clowe.

33:51.197 --> 33:53.099
You still have your Bible
I see.

33:54.833 --> 33:57.469
God has given you
very little, Ozias.

33:58.504 --> 34:01.073
Mr. Amos taught me to speak
English with this book.

34:01.707 --> 34:04.076
But God's words have taught me
so much more.

34:05.344 --> 34:06.645
God's words?

34:07.746 --> 34:10.081
(Newton)
Surely just written
by mere mortal men.

34:11.117 --> 34:12.851
It wasn't God
who came in the night

34:12.884 --> 34:14.520
And gave me food
and saved my life.

34:16.155 --> 34:18.324
You were treated so very poorly
by Mr. Clowe.

34:21.360 --> 34:24.730
I was flogged on board
his Majesty's man-of-war

34:24.763 --> 34:26.532
Ozias, for desertion.

34:27.166 --> 34:29.801
And now I'm in command
of a slave ship.

34:29.835 --> 34:31.837
I'm the captain of a slave ship.

34:35.541 --> 34:37.643
I've learned to expect
nothing from God.

34:41.213 --> 34:44.416
I remember one night,
the slave factory.

34:46.252 --> 34:47.619
I cried out in the dark

34:47.652 --> 34:50.589
Your servant listens

34:51.857 --> 34:55.261
A huge roar split the heavens,
I fell to my knees.

34:56.262 --> 34:58.630
I saw the trees bow
in His honor

34:58.664 --> 35:01.400
I heard the Lord speak my name

35:01.433 --> 35:03.402
In the rustle
of the barb leaves.

35:03.902 --> 35:05.237
God spoke to me.

35:08.174 --> 35:10.576
Tell me this, then, Ozias.

35:10.609 --> 35:13.312
Why does your just
and merciful God

35:13.745 --> 35:16.448
Condemn good people
like you and me to slavery?

35:17.949 --> 35:20.452
There are no good people,
John Newton.

35:20.952 --> 35:26.292
We are all dogs, hunted,
shackled, enslaved.

35:29.661 --> 35:32.231
That is why we need God.

35:33.265 --> 35:34.666
[Piercing shriek]

35:34.700 --> 35:36.302
(Sailor)
Captain! Captain!

35:36.335 --> 35:37.469
[Panting,
loud thumps]

35:37.503 --> 35:38.670
What's going on?

35:38.704 --> 35:40.439
He was trying
to hang himself, captain.

35:44.810 --> 35:47.646
[Slave speaking
in Gambian dialect]

35:47.679 --> 35:48.914
What is he saying?

35:49.715 --> 35:50.816
(Newton)
Ozias!

35:50.849 --> 35:51.983
He wants to die.
[Slave sobbing]

35:53.219 --> 35:55.387
Tell him we're taking him to
a better place, a new life.

35:55.421 --> 35:58.857
[Ozias speaking
in Gambian dialect]

35:59.591 --> 36:05.264
[Slave speaking
in Gambian dialect]

36:06.398 --> 36:08.200
He wants his freedom.

36:08.234 --> 36:10.569
Some of them are starving
themselves too, captain.

36:12.238 --> 36:14.273
This is valuable cargo,
Mr. Davey.

36:14.306 --> 36:15.707
I can't have slaves
killing themselves.

36:15.741 --> 36:18.644
[Heavy footsteps]

36:22.348 --> 36:23.682
Doctor?

36:23.715 --> 36:25.751
This one is gravely ill.

36:26.418 --> 36:28.520
Her son... I don't know.

36:28.554 --> 36:29.555
What is it?

36:29.588 --> 36:31.857
The flux, captain.
There's nothing to be done.

36:31.890 --> 36:36.228
[Soft murmurs and moaning]

36:40.899 --> 36:44.303
(Adira narrating)
Your great grandfather
was on that ship, Samuel.

36:44.870 --> 36:48.440
A boy struggling
to hold on to hope.

36:49.675 --> 36:53.479
His survival tied to the fate
of captain Newton.

36:55.314 --> 36:58.450
[Hooves pattering]

36:58.484 --> 36:59.985
(McGee)
Woah.

37:01.887 --> 37:03.455
I'll leave you here, Garrett.

37:03.489 --> 37:05.391
(Garrett)
McGee, you take care.

37:06.292 --> 37:07.693
Look out for Plimpton.

37:08.694 --> 37:09.895
Samuel.

37:11.730 --> 37:12.898
Godspeed, y'all.

37:13.865 --> 37:16.568
[Chains rattling,
pattering]

37:16.602 --> 37:19.605
(Musician)
Y'all take good care, now.

37:19.638 --> 37:22.408
(McGee)
You'll make it. Canaan's Land.

37:31.317 --> 37:32.484
(Garrett)
Here it is.

37:35.821 --> 37:37.423
Woah, oh.

37:37.789 --> 37:39.658
You, unhitch the horses, Samuel.

37:40.526 --> 37:41.927
(Vanessa)
Who's inside?

37:41.960 --> 37:43.895
It's a Quaker house.

37:43.929 --> 37:45.697
See that lamp?
It's safe.

37:46.998 --> 37:48.500
(Garrett)
This is where
we'll hide you tonight.

37:49.635 --> 37:51.603
[Rustling]
[Garrett sighing]

37:51.637 --> 37:53.405
- Here you go.
- Come on.

37:53.439 --> 37:55.874
[Adira coughing]

37:56.375 --> 37:57.609
(Garrett)
This way, Jim.

37:57.943 --> 37:59.678
[Knocking]

38:01.547 --> 38:02.981
[Door creaking]

38:03.014 --> 38:04.750
- Yes?
- Watchman...

38:06.885 --> 38:08.987
Morning is coming,
but also the night.

38:09.621 --> 38:11.490
[Chuckling]

38:11.523 --> 38:12.558
Come in, Mr. Garrett.

38:12.591 --> 38:14.326
- Thank you kindly.
- We've been expecting you.

38:14.360 --> 38:15.327
(Garrett)
Come on in.

38:19.531 --> 38:21.467
Here you go.
[Fire crackling]

38:22.000 --> 38:24.770
This here is Samuel Woodward
and his family. William Giddens.

38:24.803 --> 38:27.072
Come in.
You must be hungry.

38:27.105 --> 38:28.574
Very.

38:28.607 --> 38:30.609
(Missouri slave)
There are too many of us.

38:30.642 --> 38:32.444
(Giddens)
These men are from Missouri.

38:32.478 --> 38:34.713
Harriet Tubman brought them
across yesterday.

38:34.746 --> 38:37.315
We cannot all hide here.
There's not enough space.

38:37.949 --> 38:39.785
(Missouri slave)
Harriet told us that four more
free black men

38:39.818 --> 38:41.119
Were kidnapped yesterday.

38:41.152 --> 38:42.388
Now, stay calm.

38:43.589 --> 38:45.891
[Fire crackling]

38:46.157 --> 38:47.459
There you are.

38:47.493 --> 38:49.428
Where're you from?

38:49.461 --> 38:52.030
Ah, the Monroe place.
[Cutlery clicking]

38:53.164 --> 38:56.067
The biggest plantation
in the Norfolk area.

38:57.135 --> 38:58.870
We ran with Mr. Garrett's help.

38:59.605 --> 39:01.039
And God's.

39:01.072 --> 39:02.741
A chair don't build itself.

39:05.176 --> 39:07.779
[Crickets buzzing]

39:07.813 --> 39:14.420
[Band playing music
in the background]

39:16.154 --> 39:21.593
[Whistling rhythmically]

39:21.627 --> 39:23.595
Your boys at the roadblock
were right.

39:27.666 --> 39:29.468
I'll go around this way.

39:29.935 --> 39:31.503
[Loud gunshot]

39:31.803 --> 39:32.871
[Panting]

39:32.904 --> 39:33.939
(Clem)
Boss?

39:33.972 --> 39:35.040
Willie?
[Gun clicking]

39:35.073 --> 39:36.475
- You're next.
- Willie!

39:36.508 --> 39:38.810
Giddens! Giddens
is the first safe house!

39:40.211 --> 39:42.080
(Clem)
Think that Quaker is still
running a safe house?

39:42.681 --> 39:44.416
He's a bigger fool
than the Monroe boy here.

39:44.683 --> 39:47.052
Fool? You're running outta time!

39:47.519 --> 39:48.787
You told Monroe Sunday!

39:48.820 --> 39:52.023
I want no more killing!
You hear me?

39:53.892 --> 39:57.028
You clean yourself up.
We got a long ride ahead of us.

40:05.771 --> 40:08.940
[Distant shouting]
[Horses galloping]

40:10.709 --> 40:11.710
We've got visitors.

40:12.578 --> 40:13.612
Mr. Plimpton I believe.

40:13.645 --> 40:15.080
Samuel?

40:15.113 --> 40:16.782
Is there a gun, Mr. Giddens?

40:16.815 --> 40:18.617
There will be no shooting
in this house!

40:18.650 --> 40:20.752
- They're not taking us back!
- Nessa!

40:21.520 --> 40:24.089
Come on. Out the back. Hitch up
the horses to the back. Go.

40:24.122 --> 40:25.957
There's no time, Samuel.
You need to hide.

40:26.892 --> 40:28.894
- Quickly!
- There are too many of us.

40:28.927 --> 40:30.462
(Plimpton)
They'll be around here
somewhere.

40:30.496 --> 40:31.763
(Samuel)
Come on!

40:31.797 --> 40:33.499
(Garrett)
Jim, stay by me. Adira.

40:33.532 --> 40:34.966
(Missouri slave)
Let's go.

40:40.772 --> 40:42.741
Check this side
and go around the back.

40:46.077 --> 40:47.613
[Persistent knocking]

40:48.780 --> 40:50.181
What can I do for you, mister?

40:50.215 --> 40:53.652
Where's Garrett, conductor
of the Underground Railroad?

40:53.685 --> 40:55.754
(Giddens)
You should board
the train too, sir.

40:55.787 --> 40:59.124
One day we'll all stand
at the terminal before God.

40:59.157 --> 41:01.827
I don't believe in God,
Mr. Giddens.

41:01.860 --> 41:04.129
I got nothing to say to Him.

41:07.065 --> 41:10.536
[Fire crackling]
[Footsteps]

41:13.572 --> 41:15.707
[Cupboard creaking]

41:17.643 --> 41:20.879
[Metal clanging]

41:22.848 --> 41:25.684
[Floorboards creaking]

41:32.791 --> 41:34.560
[Knocking]

41:39.230 --> 41:40.766
[Gun clicking]

41:46.838 --> 41:48.073
- Clem!
- Yes, boss.

41:48.106 --> 41:49.675
I know where they are.

41:51.610 --> 41:53.278
You should never play poker,
Mr. Giddens.

41:59.651 --> 42:01.186
This isn't them.

42:01.753 --> 42:03.121
Where are they?
The others.

42:03.154 --> 42:04.790
(Giddens)
Others?

42:04.823 --> 42:06.925
The ones I came for. Garrett and
his passengers from Norfolk.

42:06.958 --> 42:08.860
- Where are they?
- I have nothing to say to you.

42:09.795 --> 42:11.763
Search the rest of the house
and the barn, and find Willie.

42:30.115 --> 42:31.750
[Gun clicking]

42:33.952 --> 42:35.787
[Thud]
[Willie grunts]

42:36.321 --> 42:37.789
Come on!

42:45.063 --> 42:47.198
You know, you may just hang
for this, Giddens.

42:47.232 --> 42:49.601
We mustn't be afraid
of death, Mr. Plimpton.

42:51.369 --> 42:54.005
Plimpton! Outside!

42:55.173 --> 42:56.608
Shi...

42:58.209 --> 43:00.378
[Horses neighing]
Go!

43:00.411 --> 43:01.847
(Plimpton)
Samuel! Don't!

43:02.748 --> 43:04.716
(Willie)
Come on! Get
Get

43:14.259 --> 43:16.127
[Heave footsteps]
[Panting]

43:16.161 --> 43:18.296
- Shoot
- Alive, I said!

43:19.430 --> 43:21.232
What a great help you were.

43:21.266 --> 43:23.034
Go hitch their horses
to the wagon.

43:23.434 --> 43:25.136
And get those slaves
tied up, now!

43:26.337 --> 43:27.372
[Giddens chuckling]

43:27.405 --> 43:30.842
I'm afraid those gentlemen
have gone, Mr. Plimpton.

43:30.876 --> 43:32.911
Out the back door.

43:32.944 --> 43:35.747
You have lost them all.
Dear, dear...

43:35.781 --> 43:37.883
You have broken
a federal law, Mr. Giddens.

43:37.916 --> 43:39.350
The slaves have gone, boss.

43:39.384 --> 43:41.286
The fugitive slave act requires

43:41.319 --> 43:44.189
That you assist in the recapture
of escaping slaves

43:44.222 --> 43:45.924
That is the law, sir.

43:45.957 --> 43:47.859
I follow my conscience,
Mr. Plimpton

43:48.259 --> 43:50.128
Whatever the consequences.

43:50.996 --> 43:54.165
We're just God fearing folk
here. That's all.

