01:06:42.832 --> 01:06:45.435
[Thunder rumbling]

01:06:55.845 --> 01:06:58.115
[Ozias groaning]

01:07:15.632 --> 01:07:17.234
Did we make it through?

01:07:18.635 --> 01:07:20.204
Yes, we did, Ozias.

01:07:24.241 --> 01:07:25.642
God protected us.

01:07:28.545 --> 01:07:30.080
Yes.

01:07:35.119 --> 01:07:36.453
Yes, He did.

01:07:37.654 --> 01:07:39.756
[Short wheezing breaths]

01:07:41.158 --> 01:07:42.759
I remember our time together

01:07:43.827 --> 01:07:46.630
Day after day working
for that monster Clowe

01:07:47.364 --> 01:07:49.266
Starved and shackled.

01:07:50.867 --> 01:07:53.303
I lost all hope.

01:07:56.373 --> 01:07:57.374
Not you.

01:07:58.575 --> 01:08:01.278
You live with strength
and determination.

01:08:06.383 --> 01:08:09.853
I owe you my life, Ozias.

01:08:12.356 --> 01:08:13.657
How can I repay you?

01:08:16.760 --> 01:08:18.528
I am a man.

01:08:21.765 --> 01:08:23.667
Am I not your brother?

01:08:26.670 --> 01:08:27.737
Yes.

01:08:29.238 --> 01:08:30.506
Yes, Ozias.

01:08:30.807 --> 01:08:34.310
[Chains rattling]

01:08:40.617 --> 01:08:42.519
My brother.

01:08:53.397 --> 01:08:56.200
By the grace of God,
I pray I'll be worthy.

01:09:00.604 --> 01:09:04.140
[Adira coughing]
[Birds cawing]

01:09:04.808 --> 01:09:06.910
I'm going home, Samuel.

01:09:07.844 --> 01:09:09.845
Finally, I'm gonna go home.

01:09:11.747 --> 01:09:12.816
No.

01:09:13.550 --> 01:09:15.519
We can all be saved.

01:09:16.620 --> 01:09:17.953
[Adira coughing]

01:09:17.987 --> 01:09:21.291
No, no, hang on, ma.
Drink. Drink. Drink.

01:09:24.928 --> 01:09:27.796
[Grunting]

01:09:34.770 --> 01:09:39.175
I..., I want you to have these.

01:09:41.377 --> 01:09:46.283
The Bible belonged
to your great grandfather

01:09:46.716 --> 01:09:48.885
A gift from Mr. Newton himself.

01:09:51.688 --> 01:09:53.890
Read the Bible.

01:09:56.426 --> 01:09:58.828
How sweet the sound.

01:10:04.501 --> 01:10:08.872
[Faintly]
You are not alone.

01:10:17.781 --> 01:10:20.550
[Sobbing]

01:10:24.821 --> 01:10:26.590
[Sniffling]

01:10:33.363 --> 01:10:35.765
[Thunder rolling]
[Rain pattering]

01:10:42.038 --> 01:10:44.408
(Vanessa)
You're free now, Adira.

01:10:48.745 --> 01:10:50.880
There's no God for us.

01:10:50.914 --> 01:10:53.650
Samuel, no.

01:10:53.983 --> 01:10:56.453
Shh...
[Sniffling]

01:11:01.691 --> 01:11:04.861
[Thunder rumbling loudly]

01:11:05.429 --> 01:11:07.664
[Horse neighing]
They'll head for Buffalo

01:11:07.697 --> 01:11:10.500
Cross into Canada there,
over the Niagara river.

01:11:11.100 --> 01:11:12.769
Free?

01:11:13.437 --> 01:11:14.938
Over my dead body, Clem.

01:11:15.705 --> 01:11:17.607
They'll be meeting up with
Douglass at his church in town.

01:11:18.708 --> 01:11:20.444
Why'd you quit?

01:11:20.477 --> 01:11:23.580
I heard you caught a free black
man and killed him by mistake.

01:11:24.348 --> 01:11:25.815
Whatever you say, Willie.

01:11:26.616 --> 01:11:28.585
I think all coloreds
should be slaves...

01:11:32.088 --> 01:11:34.458
(Willie)
Any man who thinks otherwise
is a damn fool.

01:11:37.794 --> 01:11:40.364
This is just a great big game
for you, innit boy?

01:11:40.397 --> 01:11:41.798
Coloreds just got
the better of you?

01:11:41.831 --> 01:11:43.700
[Loud thump]
[Grunting]

01:11:44.100 --> 01:11:45.602
[Willie coughing]

01:11:47.471 --> 01:11:50.607
That's it, old man! There's
the Plimpton from the stories.

01:11:51.007 --> 01:11:52.709
Not the slave sympathizer

01:11:52.742 --> 01:11:54.378
Who's running his hunt
like he's the Railroad condu...

01:11:54.411 --> 01:11:55.612
[Thump]

01:11:55.645 --> 01:11:57.080
Willie!
[Willie coughing]

01:11:57.881 --> 01:11:59.583
Enough, Willie.

01:12:05.922 --> 01:12:07.323
(Willie)
You keep, old man.

01:12:08.492 --> 01:12:11.327
I'm riding to town.
Do what we came here for.

01:12:14.464 --> 01:12:17.434
[Crickets chirping]

01:12:17.467 --> 01:12:21.337
(Vanessa)
Hey, Samuel, we're so close.
Have faith.

01:12:22.071 --> 01:12:24.508
Mr. Douglass will help us.

01:12:25.542 --> 01:12:28.044
Help us what?
Run some more?

01:12:31.548 --> 01:12:33.717
Probably gonna
run us down, Nessa.

01:12:34.951 --> 01:12:37.821
They gonna beat us, they gonna
put the collar to us again.

01:12:38.888 --> 01:12:40.757
Adira said have faith.

01:12:41.024 --> 01:12:43.059
[Scoffs]
Faith...

01:12:44.661 --> 01:12:46.463
Look what good that did her.

01:12:47.163 --> 01:12:48.832
No.

01:12:48.865 --> 01:12:51.034
No, death saved her
from where we're going.

01:12:51.067 --> 01:12:54.404
Sammy, stop, please stop!
Not here! Not now.

01:12:54.438 --> 01:12:57.907
Why? Why God chose us
to be half human?

01:12:57.941 --> 01:13:00.677
To be strung up whenever
they want? Huh?

01:13:00.710 --> 01:13:02.846
To work all our lives
and to die?

01:13:04.013 --> 01:13:07.651
No. This church, this church,
this church means nothing!

01:13:07.684 --> 01:13:09.653
This church means nothing to us!

01:13:09.686 --> 01:13:11.455
It ain't done nothing for us!

01:13:11.488 --> 01:13:12.889
- We have Jim.
- I don't wanna hear that.

01:13:12.922 --> 01:13:14.791
You should hold on for Jim

01:13:14.824 --> 01:13:16.993
And hold on for me,
hold on to me!

01:13:17.827 --> 01:13:19.963
Hold on to God!

01:13:36.646 --> 01:13:38.815
* Not a second

01:13:41.485 --> 01:13:43.419
* Or another minute

01:13:46.155 --> 01:13:48.091
* Not an hour

01:13:50.226 --> 01:13:52.195
* Or another day

01:13:56.833 --> 01:13:59.002
* But at this moment

01:14:00.670 --> 01:14:03.973
* With my arms outstretched

01:14:07.243 --> 01:14:08.878
* I need you

01:14:10.780 --> 01:14:12.649
* To make a way

01:14:14.984 --> 01:14:18.955
* As you have done

01:14:20.624 --> 01:14:23.226
* So many times before

01:14:25.228 --> 01:14:29.766
* Through a window
or an open door *

01:14:32.035 --> 01:14:37.006
* I stretch my hands to thee

01:14:40.577 --> 01:14:42.679
* Oh, come rescue me

01:14:45.314 --> 01:14:50.253
* I need you right away

01:14:57.661 --> 01:14:58.928
(Douglass)
Vanessa?

01:15:01.197 --> 01:15:02.732
Mr. Douglass.

01:15:04.200 --> 01:15:05.769
Oh, I'm sorry.

01:15:08.738 --> 01:15:11.708
I'm dead to him, sir. I'm dead.

01:15:13.777 --> 01:15:15.178
He needs you more than ever now.

01:15:16.112 --> 01:15:17.747
He needs all your strength.

01:15:18.815 --> 01:15:22.118
Ma, I saw pa,
he's outside, and he's...

01:15:22.151 --> 01:15:24.287
I'll go to him.
Stay here.

01:15:25.121 --> 01:15:27.090
Plimpton won't like this,
Willie.

01:15:27.123 --> 01:15:28.925
It's been two weeks.

01:15:29.593 --> 01:15:31.260
Plimpton won't mind a bunch
of dogs get the better of him.

01:15:37.300 --> 01:15:38.602
Samuel.

01:15:39.068 --> 01:15:40.904
[Dramatic music]

01:15:40.937 --> 01:15:43.573
This is it.
Let's get

01:15:46.810 --> 01:15:49.112
You're telling me you rode off
and you left the others there.

01:15:49.846 --> 01:15:51.815
- We got Samuel.
- That's what you're telling me?

01:15:51.848 --> 01:15:53.883
They could be halfway
to the state line by now!

01:15:53.917 --> 01:15:55.919
(Plimpton)
What good is he without her?

01:15:56.285 --> 01:15:58.988
And what use is Douglass? Huh?

01:16:02.391 --> 01:16:04.894
Samuel, you're causing me a hell
of a headache, you know that?

01:16:06.930 --> 01:16:08.932
Well, unfortunately
I need all of yous.

01:16:09.666 --> 01:16:12.001
Something that Monroe's watchdog
here don't seem to understand.

01:16:12.669 --> 01:16:14.203
Yeah, but we got him.
[Chuckling]

01:16:15.639 --> 01:16:17.040
Back up!

01:16:17.306 --> 01:16:20.109
Drop it! Drop it!

01:16:20.143 --> 01:16:22.011
- Drop it!
- Okay, alright!

01:16:22.045 --> 01:16:24.180
Look, you hold all the cards
here, Samuel. Look.

01:16:24.213 --> 01:16:26.816
- There you go.
- You too! Drop it!

01:16:28.685 --> 01:16:30.219
Now you untie him.

01:16:32.121 --> 01:16:34.590
You're gonna be running
your whole life, you know that?

01:16:35.692 --> 01:16:38.194
Monroe will never stop looking
for that little bitch of his.

01:16:38.227 --> 01:16:39.796
[Grunting]

01:16:41.197 --> 01:16:43.166
You better shoot me now cause
we gonna hunt you down like
dogs.

01:16:45.835 --> 01:16:47.303
Samuel!
[Gun clicking]

01:16:48.705 --> 01:16:50.373
(Douglass)
You will never be free.

01:16:59.448 --> 01:17:00.917
Come on. Come on!

01:17:04.053 --> 01:17:06.289
- Remember what I said, Samuel.
- Don't move!

01:17:11.360 --> 01:17:13.897
[Door creaking]

01:17:14.263 --> 01:17:17.133
[Footsteps]

01:17:17.166 --> 01:17:19.769
You must go quickly.
There's not much time.

01:17:42.091 --> 01:17:43.827
(Adira narrating)
You're nearly there, Samuel.

01:17:46.329 --> 01:17:50.133
With forgiveness
comes true freedom.

01:17:52.736 --> 01:17:55.038
I'll tell you, boy. Move!

01:17:55.805 --> 01:17:57.941
[Chains rattling]

01:17:59.408 --> 01:18:02.211
[Indistinct chatter]
[Footsteps]

01:18:13.757 --> 01:18:15.224
(Newton)
Did you find him, Bosun?

01:18:15.258 --> 01:18:17.060
Yes, I just left Mr. Barton.

01:18:17.093 --> 01:18:19.095
He sends his regards
and congratulations.

01:18:20.797 --> 01:18:23.032
- Congratulations?
- On a successful maiden voyage.

01:18:23.366 --> 01:18:24.968
Only 24 dead.

01:18:25.001 --> 01:18:27.003
Yes, sir. And 16 with the flux

01:18:27.036 --> 01:18:28.838
God knows
how long they will live.

01:18:29.839 --> 01:18:30.874
Congratulations.

01:18:34.944 --> 01:18:39.983
[Indistinct chatter]
[Chains rattling]

01:18:41.184 --> 01:18:44.387
[Footsteps on gravel]

01:18:45.288 --> 01:18:47.023
[Man murmuring indistinctly]

01:18:47.423 --> 01:18:51.895
I want that one and that one.

01:18:55.999 --> 01:18:58.734
[Horse hooves pattering]

01:18:59.302 --> 01:19:01.104
Excellent choice, Charisma.

01:19:01.137 --> 01:19:02.906
Thank you, father.

01:19:02.939 --> 01:19:04.240
[Smacking sound]

01:19:05.541 --> 01:19:07.944
[Crunching gravel]

01:19:07.977 --> 01:19:09.913
(Seaton)
137 and 38.

01:19:09.946 --> 01:19:11.881
(Charisma)
Thank you kindly, sir.

01:19:11.915 --> 01:19:13.182
(Slave trader)
Thank you.

01:19:16.219 --> 01:19:18.021
[Chains rattling]

01:19:28.231 --> 01:19:29.365
Safe.

01:19:30.233 --> 01:19:31.901
Get back, 149.

01:19:33.302 --> 01:19:35.171
You must go with them now.

01:19:35.438 --> 01:19:37.073
Take this. It's a gift.

01:19:43.847 --> 01:19:45.481
We sail on the tide, Mr. Davey.

01:19:46.349 --> 01:19:49.552
(Slave trader)
Up on the block now
we have slave number 149.

01:19:49.585 --> 01:19:52.355
Male, age 11 years old,
no signs of flux.

01:19:53.022 --> 01:19:54.924
Let's sell him.
Let me hear 20 dollars. 20.

01:19:57.193 --> 01:20:00.196
(Minister)
Do thee love her, comfort her

01:20:00.529 --> 01:20:04.567
Honor and keep her
in sickness and in health

01:20:06.235 --> 01:20:08.838
So long as you both shall live?

01:20:09.238 --> 01:20:10.273
I do.

01:20:20.984 --> 01:20:22.151
You all know me.

01:20:24.888 --> 01:20:28.124
But I'm not the same man who
left Rochester ten months ago.

01:20:30.493 --> 01:20:32.962
That John Newton
was dramatically changed

01:20:32.996 --> 01:20:36.832
One night in a storm
on the Atlantic ocean.

01:20:38.367 --> 01:20:42.238
(Newton)
In utter despair I cried out
and was given another chance.

01:20:47.143 --> 01:20:49.145
Take away a toy from a child

01:20:49.178 --> 01:20:51.347
And give him another

01:20:51.380 --> 01:20:53.416
And he is satisfied.

01:20:55.284 --> 01:20:57.853
But if he be hungry,
no toy will do.

01:20:59.956 --> 01:21:02.625
Thus, as newborn babes

01:21:03.392 --> 01:21:06.229
True believers desire
the sincere milk of the word.

01:21:08.064 --> 01:21:10.566
And the desire of grace
in this way

01:21:12.035 --> 01:21:13.469
Is grace.

01:21:16.940 --> 01:21:20.043
* Amazing Grace

01:21:21.610 --> 01:21:25.214
* How sweet the sound

01:21:27.250 --> 01:21:33.122
* That saved a wretch like me

01:21:35.358 --> 01:21:38.194
* I once was lost

01:21:39.462 --> 01:21:42.598
* But now am found

01:21:44.033 --> 01:21:46.269
* Was blind

01:21:46.302 --> 01:21:49.538
* But now I see

01:21:52.308 --> 01:21:56.279
[Gentle background music]

01:21:56.312 --> 01:21:59.983
[Hooves pattering]
[Carriage rattling]

01:22:07.056 --> 01:22:09.558
(Jim)
Look, pa!
I can see the crossing.

01:22:10.693 --> 01:22:14.063
[Water lapping]

01:22:22.671 --> 01:22:24.240
Hey!

01:22:30.579 --> 01:22:33.482
Go on, Samuel.
Get Jim across, I'll wait here.

01:22:34.317 --> 01:22:36.585
Come on, boy. Let's go.

01:22:36.619 --> 01:22:38.254
We're free, son!

01:22:41.224 --> 01:22:42.525
We're free!

01:22:48.431 --> 01:22:49.365
Got you, boy.

01:22:56.772 --> 01:22:58.074
[Vanessa yells]
Hey, boy!

01:23:00.076 --> 01:23:01.244
Come on back now, boy.

01:23:01.577 --> 01:23:02.711
Nessa!

01:23:02.745 --> 01:23:04.380
(Willie)
Don't make me do
something stupid.

01:23:05.381 --> 01:23:06.682
Come on!

01:23:09.552 --> 01:23:10.486
Willie!

01:23:11.820 --> 01:23:14.090
Clem, are you with me?
We'll split Monroe's money.

01:23:14.123 --> 01:23:16.659
They're mine.
No more killing, I mean it.

01:23:17.326 --> 01:23:19.595
Monroe told me dead
or alive, old man.

01:23:20.496 --> 01:23:22.398
Clem, you're just gonna
stand there?

01:23:22.431 --> 01:23:23.732
You best get outta here, Clem.

01:23:25.701 --> 01:23:27.403
I ain't gonna ask again.

01:23:27.836 --> 01:23:29.672
[Gun clicking]

01:23:32.175 --> 01:23:34.077
So you're just gonna shoot
Monroe's daughter, huh?

01:23:35.378 --> 01:23:37.246
I'm all yours, Mr. Plimpton!

01:23:37.646 --> 01:23:39.482
Shut your mouth, slave boy.
No deals!

01:23:39.515 --> 01:23:40.716
Tell him not to do it,
Mr. Plimpton.

01:23:40.749 --> 01:23:44.753
Shut your mouth, nigger!
[Gunshots firing]

01:23:44.787 --> 01:23:46.422
(Samuel)
Nessa!

01:23:47.356 --> 01:23:49.292
- Samuel!
- Come over here.

01:23:49.492 --> 01:23:50.693
Come on.

01:24:05.574 --> 01:24:08.177
[Plimpton panting]

01:24:08.211 --> 01:24:09.778
Why, Mr Plimpton?

01:24:12.715 --> 01:24:14.283
I've had enough.

01:24:15.684 --> 01:24:17.353
(Plimpton)
No more killing.

01:24:19.488 --> 01:24:20.723
[Plimpton grunts]

01:24:22.691 --> 01:24:25.194
Monroe gave me this
to bring you in.

01:24:25.894 --> 01:24:27.363
Take it.

01:24:31.700 --> 01:24:35.204
Make a life for her
and your son.

01:24:38.174 --> 01:24:40.176
It's a little gift
from his grandfather.

01:24:41.644 --> 01:24:43.212
Huh?

01:24:44.713 --> 01:24:47.150
[Heavy breathing]

01:24:48.151 --> 01:24:49.485
You're free now, Samuel.

01:25:05.468 --> 01:25:07.636
[Soft pattering]

01:25:22.485 --> 01:25:25.354
(Adira narrating)
How sweet the sound...

01:25:25.388 --> 01:25:28.524
[Soft background music]

01:25:53.416 --> 01:25:58.153
* Amazing Grace

01:25:58.554 --> 01:26:01.890
* How sweet the sound

01:26:03.559 --> 01:26:09.532
* That saved a wretch like me

01:26:13.702 --> 01:26:17.673
* I once was lost
[Voice breaking]

01:26:19.275 --> 01:26:22.711
* But now am found

01:26:23.679 --> 01:26:29.485
* Was blind
But now I... *

01:26:38.394 --> 01:26:43.632
[Choir singing
Amazing Grace]

